chronitem.event:
Leads local opposition to the March 1804 act of Congress that provided
                        for partition of Louisiana territory, restrictions on the import of slaves,
                        and deferred admittance to the Union

scopecontent.p:
Includes deeds, releases, leases, agreements, rent rolls, and surveys
                                for lands in Dutchess County, the Woodstock area, New Stamford,
                                Hurley, the Saratoga Patent, and Livingston Manor.
